37 /**
38  * Trait to help with caching objects in the wookie-cache
39  * A cacheable object will be converted to JSON and then stored as Array[Byte] in the cache manager
40  *
41  * TODO: Need to implement timeout strategies. Currently it simply times out the object based on when it
42  * was inserted. This can cause an object to constantly be updating the insert time and possibly never timeout.
43  * Also need to implement a strategy where everything will time out every hour or something like that.
44  */
45 trait Cacheable[T] extends Serializable {
46   this : Serializable =>
47 
48   // This is a wrapper object that will basically wrap the object with an insertion time and any other meta data that it may require
49   @SerialVersionUID(10L)
50   protected case class CacheWrapper(data:Array[Byte], insertionTime:Long=0L) extends Serializable
51 
52   @transient implicit def liftJsonFormats = DefaultFormats.lossless + NoTypeHints ++ JodaTimeSerializers.all
53   @transient implicit val timeout = Timeout(Duration(1, "seconds"))
54 
55   /**
56    * Gets the timeout for the data in the cache, by default will be set to 0L which means it will never time out
57    * The value is in milliseconds
58    *
59    * @return milliseconds for timeout of data in cache
60    */
61   def dataTimeout : Long = -1L
62 
63   /**
64    * The key used to cache the object
65    *
66    * @return
67    */
68   def key : String = ???
69 
70   /**
71    * The namespace used for the object
72    *
73    * @return
74    */
75   def namespace : String = ???
76 
77   /**
78    * Extract function allows cacheable object to have control how it extracts the byte data from the array
79    * by default it will try and parse it as a JSON object and then extract it to the class type
80    *
81    * @param obj the array of bytes
82    * @return
83    */
84   protected def extract(obj:Array[Byte])(implicit m: Manifest[T]) : Option[T] = {
85     Some(JsonParser.parse(new String(obj, StandardCharsets.UTF_8)).extract[T])
86   }
87 
88   /**
89    * getBytes function allows cacheable object to have control over how it writes the data to memcache
90    * By default it will use Lift JSON to decompose then render the object from json to a string and
91    * then simply call getBytes on the string
92    *
93    * @return
94    */
95   protected def getBytes : Array[Byte] = {
96     compactRender(decompose(this)).getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8)
97   }
98 
99   /**
100    * Checks to see if the object that was stored in the cache is past the timeout, if it
101    * is then then false else true, if timeout is 0L then assumes no timeout and will always return true
102    *
103    * @param insertionTime the time the object was inserted into the cache
104    * @return true if current time subtract the timeout for the object is less than or equal too the time the object
105    *         was inserted into the cache
106    */
107   protected def checkTimeout(insertionTime:Long) : Boolean = {
108     if (dataTimeout < 0 || compat.Platform.currentTime - dataTimeout <= insertionTime) {
109       true
110     } else {
111       false
112     }
113   }
114 
115   def readFromCacheSelect(cacheRef:ActorSelection, cacheKey:Option[CacheKey]=None)
116       (implicit timeout:Timeout, executor:ExecutionContext, m:Manifest[T]) : Future[Option[T]] = {
117     val p = Promise[Option[T]]
118     cacheRef.resolveOne onComplete {
119       case Success(s) =>
120         readFromCache(s, cacheKey)(timeout, executor, m) onComplete {
121           case Success(result) => p success result
122           case Failure(f) =>
123             p success None
124             throw f
125         }
126       case Failure(f) =>
127         p success None
128         throw f
129     }
130     p.future
131   }
132 
133   /**
134    * Looks in the supplied cache for the current object
135    *
136    * @param cacheRef This is a reference to the cache actor
137    * @param timeout Timeout for the cache read
138    * @return
139    */
140   def readFromCache(cacheRef:ActorRef, cacheKey:Option[CacheKey]=None)
141       (implicit timeout:Timeout, executor:ExecutionContext, m:Manifest[T]) : Future[Option[T]] = {
142     val ck = getCacheKey(cacheKey)
143     val p = Promise[Option[T]]
144     val future = Patterns.ask(cacheRef, Get(namespace, ck), timeout).mapTo[Option[ChannelBuffer]]
145     future onComplete {
146       case Success(s) =>
147         unwrapData(s) match {
148           case Some(s) => p success Some(s)
149           case None =>
150             cacheRef ! Delete(namespace, ck)
151             p success None
152         }
153       case Failure(f) => throw f
154     }
155     p.future
156   }
157 
158   def writeInCacheSelect(cacheRef:ActorSelection, cacheKey:Option[CacheKey]=None)
159       (implicit timeout:Timeout, executor:ExecutionContext) : Future[Boolean] = {
160     val p = Promise[Boolean]
161     cacheRef.resolveOne onComplete {
162       case Success(s) =>
163         writeInCache(s, cacheKey)(timeout, executor) onComplete {
164           case Success(s) => p success true
165           case Failure(f) => p success false
166         }
167       case Failure(f) => throw f
168     }
169     p.future
170   }
171 
172   /**
173    * Writes the current object to the supplied cache
174    *
175    * @param cacheRef This is a reference to the cache actor
176    * @param timeout Timeout for the cache read
177    * @return
178    */
179   def writeInCache(cacheRef:ActorRef, cacheKey:Option[CacheKey]=None)
180       (implicit timeout:Timeout, executor:ExecutionContext) : Future[Boolean] = {
181     val p = Promise[Boolean]
182     val future = Patterns.ask(cacheRef, Add(namespace, getCacheKey(cacheKey), wrapData), timeout).mapTo[Boolean]
183     future onComplete {
184       case Success(s) => p success true
185       case Failure(f) =>
186         p failure f
187         throw f
188     }
189     p.future
190   }
191 
192   /**
193    * Deletes the current item from the cache
194    *
195    * @param cacheRef The is a reference to the cache actor
196    * @param cacheKey Optional key, usually this is managed by the object itself
197    * @param timeout timeout for the cache delete response
198    * @param executor the executor
199    * @return true if delete was successful
200    */
201   def deleteFromCache(cacheRef:ActorRef, cacheKey:Option[CacheKey]=None)
202       (implicit timeout:Timeout, executor:ExecutionContext) : Future[Boolean] = {
203     val p = Promise[Boolean]
204     val future = Patterns.ask(cacheRef, Delete(namespace, getCacheKey(cacheKey)), timeout).mapTo[Boolean]
205     future onComplete {
206       case Success(s) => p success true
207       case Failure(f) =>
208         p failure f
209         throw f
210     }
211     p.future
212   }
213 
214   private def wrapData : ChannelBuffer = {
215     val wrapper = CacheWrapper(this.getBytes, compat.Platform.currentTime)
216     ChannelBuffers.wrappedBuffer(wrapper.pickle.value)
217   }
218 
219   private def unwrapData(data:Option[ChannelBuffer])(implicit m:Manifest[T]) : Option[T] = {
220     data match {
221       case Some(buffer) =>
222         val wrapper = buffer.array.unpickle[CacheWrapper]
223         extract(wrapper.data) match {
224           case Some(value) =>
225             if (checkTimeout(wrapper.insertionTime)) {
226               Some(value)
227             } else {
228               None
229             }
230           case None => None
231         }
232       case None => None
233     }
234   }
235 
236   protected def getCacheKey(cacheKey:Option[CacheKey]) : String = {
237     cacheKey match {
238       case Some(s) => s.toString
239       case None => key
240     }
241   }
242 }
